75
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,872
current VLM struggle with this.

76
00:02:50,496 --> 00:02:52,909
Therefore, we identify three key

77
00:02:52,909 --> 00:02:54,840
challenges. First, virtual physical

78
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:57,736
ambiguity. Without a mechanism to separate

79
00:02:57,736 --> 00:03:00,149
projected virtual content from physical

80
00:03:00,149 --> 00:03:02,563
environment, VLM suffer from virtual

81
00:03:02,563 --> 00:03:04,493
physical ambiguity causing "merged"

82
00:03:04,493 --> 00:03:05,941
descriptions. Second, perceptual

83
00:03:05,941 --> 00:03:08,355
degradation due to projection. Various

84
00:03:08,355 --> 00:03:10,286
geometric and photometric distortions

85
00:03:10,436 --> 00:03:12,776
degrade image quality. This makes standard

86
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:15,116
VLM captioning unreliable. Third, lack of

87
00:03:15,116 --> 00:03:17,846
SAR semantic benchmark dataset. There is

88
00:03:17,846 --> 00:03:20,186
a lack of large-scale semantically

89
00:03:20,186 --> 00:03:22,916
annotated dataset required to train and

90
00:03:22,916 --> 00:03:25,256
evaluate models to interpret the complex

91
00:03:25,256 --> 00:03:26,036
SAR scenes.

92
00:03:27,181 --> 00:03:30,044
To address these, we propose: first,

93
00:03:30,044 --> 00:03:32,907
ProCap framework two-stage pipeline

94
00:03:32,907 --> 00:03:35,292
that decouples projection content from

95
00:03:35,292 --> 00:03:37,678
physical scene via segmentation and

96
00:03:37,678 --> 00:03:40,541
region-aware retrieval. Second, RGB dataset

97
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:43,404
, the first large-scale SAR

98
00:03:43,404 --> 00:03:46,267
semantic benchmark with 65 scenes and

99
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:48,936
above 180,000 projections. Last,

100
00:03:48,936 --> 00:03:51,677
dual-captioning protocol, task specific

101
00:03:51,677 --> 00:03:54,418
tokens enable independent evaluation of

102
00:03:54,418 --> 00:03:56,611
scene and projection descriptions.

103
